#. <section class="sutta" id="sn52.11"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn52.11:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 52"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 52"

#. </p><p>
#. VAR: 2. Dutiyavagga → sahassavaggo (bj)
msgctxt "sn52.11:0.2"
msgid "2. Dutiyavagga"
msgstr "2. A Thousand"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 11. Kappasahassasutta → sahassasuttaṃ (bj) | sahassa (pts1)
msgctxt "sn52.11:0.3"
msgid "11. Kappasahassasutta"
msgstr "11. A Thousand Aeons"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn52.11:1.1"
msgid ""
"Ekaṃ samayaṃ āyasmā anuruddho sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa "
"ārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time Venerable Anuruddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, "
"Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery."

msgctxt "sn52.11:1.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho sambahulā bhikkhū yenāyasmā anuruddho tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; "
"upasaṅkamitvā āyasmatā anuruddhena saddhiṃ … pe … ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho te "
"bhikkhū āyasmantaṃ anuruddhaṃ etadavocuṃ:"
msgstr ""
"Then several mendicants went up to Venerable Anuruddha, exchanged greetings "
"with him … and said:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn52.11:2.1"
msgid ""
"“Katamesaṃ āyasmā anuruddho dhammānaṃ bhāvitattā bahulīkatattā mahābhiññataṃ "
"patto”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“What things has Venerable Anuruddha developed and cultivated to attain "
"great direct knowledge?”"

msgctxt "sn52.11:2.2"
msgid ""
"“Catunnaṃ khvāhaṃ, āvuso, satipaṭṭhānānaṃ bhāvitattā bahulīkatattā "
"mahābhiññataṃ patto."
msgstr ""
"“Reverends, I attained great direct knowledge by developing and cultivating "
"the four kinds of mindfulness meditation."

msgctxt "sn52.11:2.3"
msgid "Katamesaṃ catunnaṃ?"
msgstr "What four?"

msgctxt "sn52.11:2.4"
msgid "Idhāhaṃ, āvuso, kāye kāyānupassī viharāmi … pe …"
msgstr "I meditate observing an aspect of the body …"

msgctxt "sn52.11:2.5"
msgid "vedanāsu … pe …"
msgstr "feelings …"

msgctxt "sn52.11:2.6"
msgid "citte … pe …"
msgstr "mind …"

msgctxt "sn52.11:2.7"
msgid ""
"dhammesu dhammānupassī viharāmi ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke "
"abhijjhādomanassaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"principles—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the "
"world."

msgctxt "sn52.11:2.8"
msgid ""
"imesaṃ khvāhaṃ, āvuso, catunnaṃ satipaṭṭhānānaṃ bhāvitattā bahulīkatattā "
"mahābhiññataṃ patto."
msgstr ""
"I attained great direct knowledge by developing and cultivating these four "
"kinds of mindfulness meditation."

msgctxt "sn52.11:2.9"
msgid ""
"Imesañca panāhaṃ, āvuso, catunnaṃ satipaṭṭhānānaṃ bhāvitattā bahulīkatattā "
"kappasahassaṃ anussarāmī”ti."
msgstr ""
"And it’s because of developing and cultivating these four kinds of "
"mindfulness meditation that I recollect a thousand aeons.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn52.11:2.10"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
